programme.title: Who Do You Think You Are?

programme.title: EuropeanChampionships2018
programme.desc: Coverage of day two of the inaugural multi-sports event from Glasgow, featuring gymnastics, synchronised swimming, swimming and rowing. The SSE Hydro will host the gymnastics events, as the qualification for the junior women individual apparatus finals is scheduled to begin, while the team free preliminary event in the synchronised swimming is scheduled for Scotstoun Sports Campus. A number of rowing repechages and semi-finals are due to take place at Strathclyde Country Park, including the women's and men's pair and four categories, as well as a number of sculls races. Meanwhile, the swimming heats commence at Tollcross International Swimming Centre, featuring the women's and men's 100m breaststroke, women's 400m individual medley, and men's 400m freestyle. Presented by Clare MacNamara, with analysis from Andrew Bree, Earl McCarthy, Grainne Murphy, Martyn Irvine, Neville Maxwell and Sinead Jennings

programme.title: EuropeanChampionships2018
programme.desc: Further coverage of day two of the inaugural multi-sports event from Glasgow, featuring gymnastics, synchronised swimming, swimming and cycling. The Sir Chris Hoy Velodrome will play host to a number of races today, focusing on the women's and men's team sprint, team pursuit, and scratch race disciplines. Elsewhere, the junior women's gymnastics continues with the qualification for individual apparatus, followed by the team final and all around final, while two synchronised swimming finals are due to take place with the duet technical final and mixed duet technical final. Meanwhile, the swimming event continues and is set to feature the finals of the women's 400m individual medley and 4x100m freestyle relay disciplines, as well as the men's 400m freestyle and 4x100m freestyle relay categories. programme.desc: A dancer tries to balance her dreams of stardom with her devotion to her old neighborhood. Rappers Missy Elliott, Ginuwine and Jadakiss have cameos

programme.title: You Got Served
programme.desc: The members of the now-defunct R&B group B2K star in this frenzied saga about street-dancers who compete in impromptu contests judged by the public. Omari Grandberry and Marques Houston star as the team's leaders, who have a falling out when one begins romancing the other's sister

programme.title: Step Up
programme.desc: A sullen young thug named Tyler winds up doing community service at the Baltimore High School for the Performing Arts. At first he's just smirking and mopping the floors, but then Nora, a talented dancer and choreographer, loses her partner to a fractured ankle mere weeks before the big showcase, and Tyler steps in as her partner. At first he doesn't take it too seriously but then again, he's never had a real chance in life. His best friend from the street gets jealous..

programme.title: The Zookeeper's Wife
programme.desc: A husband and wife in Nazi-occupied Poland use their position as caretakers at the Warsaw Zoo to shepherd Jews out of the country. Based on the non-fiction book by Diane Ackerman ("A Natural History of the Senses")

programme.title: Nell
programme.desc: A young woman living in an isolated North Carolina cabin is discovered by a small-town doctor, who is fascinated by her and attempts to introduce her to the world. Based on the play "Idioglossia" by Mark Handley

programme.title: Shakespeare in Love
programme.desc: One of the wittiest, most charming film comedies ever made, Shakespeare in Love is a brilliantly fictional story behind the creation of one of the most enduring pieces of literature ever written by the most acclaimed writer of all-time. Plagued with debt, writer's block, and fallen far past deadline for his latest play, it seems like things can't get much worse for young William Shakespeare (Joseph Fiennes). Then Will meets Viola, a young lady masquerading as man

programme.title: The Mummy Returns
programme.desc: Adventurer Rick O'Connell (Brendan Fraser) once again battles the resurrected mummy in this sequel to the 1999 hit. Loud, absurd escapist fare with kitschy special effects. Evelyn “Evie” O'Connell: Rachel Weisz. Jonathan Carnahan: John Hannah. Stephen Sommers directed

programme.title: Lara Croft Tomb Raider
programme.desc: In this sequel to Lara Croft: Tomb Raider, British archaeologist Lara Croft (Angelina Jolie) has made an important archaeological discovery: an orb that leads to the mythical Pandora's Box. Unfortunately, mad scientist Jonathan Reiss is also after the box willing to open it as his ultimate weapon. Recruited by British Intelligence, Croft will go into a journey that includes Hong Kong, Kenya, Tanzania, Greece and China, to stop the evil Reiss and save the world

programme.title: The Outsiders
programme.desc: Members of rival local gangs, distinguished by the haves and the have-nots, get into a scuffle that results in death in 1960s Oklahoma

programme.title: The Wicker Man
programme.desc: Remake of the cult British thriller. A police sergeant visits a remote island off the Washington coast to search for a missing girl, but begins to fear for her safety when he finds the local community in thrall to paganism and mysterious beliefs. The sergeant's unease grows when the islanders deny the girl's existence and attempt to obstruct his investigation

programme.title: Empire
programme.desc: Gangster thriller following a New York drug dealer who hopes to make a legal fortune on Wall Street. When a stockbroker offers him a business proposal, he thinks this will be his chance to go out on top, but soon finds out that he has been double-crossed and his last option is to get revenge

programme.title: The Mummy
programme.desc: Fantasy adventure about the search for buried treasure protected by an ancient mummy's curse in the Egyptian desert. An American mercenary who knows the treasure's secret location is rescued from a Cairo prison by an English historian and her brother. Racing against unscrupulous rivals, they head into the desert, where they encounter flesh-eating scarab beetles, killer sandstorms and reincarnated demons

programme.title: Born on the Fourth of July
programme.desc: Oliver Stone's docudrama about paralyzed Vietnam vet Ron Kovic, who tries to reconcile memories of his idealistic youth with his post-war disillusionment

programme.title: Collateral
programme.desc: A character study-turned-thriller about a cabdriver who ferries a hit man on a late-night killing spree in Los Angeles. Foxx was nominated for Best Supporting Actor

programme.title: John Wick
programme.desc: Hit man John Wick is once again called out of retirement, this time by a former colleague who wants him to repay a debt by killing an Italian crime lord. But when the assassination goes awry, Wick finds himself hunted by an international cabal of killers, and his only hope for survival might be a shadowy figure known as the Bowery King

programme.title: John Wick
programme.desc: Hit man John Wick is once again called out of retirement, this time by a former colleague who wants him to repay a debt by killing an Italian crime lord. But when the assassination goes awry, Wick finds himself hunted by an international cabal of killers, and his only hope for survival might be a shadowy figure known as the Bowery King

programme.title: The Scorpion King
programme.desc: Inspired by the legendary Egyptian warrior, The Scorpion King is set 5000 years ago in the notorious city of Gomorrah, where an evil ruler is determined to lay waste to all the nomadic people of the desert. The few remaining tribes, never natural allies, have to unite or perish. Knowing their enemy relies on the visions of the sorcerer, they hire a skilled assassin, Mathayus (Dwayne Johnson), to eliminate the visionary

programme.title: Seed of Chucky
programme.desc: Maniacal doll Chucky (voice of Brad Dourif) and his bride (voice of Jennifer Tilly) go on a killing spree in Hollywood after being resurrected by their gentle offspring. A wooden horror yarn with wit. Tilly also stars as herself; indie filmmaker John Waters appears as a paparazzo. The fifth film in the horror series. Don Mancini, who created the series, makes his directorial debut

programme.title: Confidence
programme.desc: Well-made but derivative crime drama about a cocky grifter (Edward Burns) trying to make amends after accidentally ripping off a powerful L.A. underworld boss (Dustin Hoffman). Directed by James Foley. Screenplay by Doug Jung

programme.title: About a Boy
programme.desc: Adaptation of the Nick Hornby novel about the friendship that develops between a bright but awkward 12-year-old boy and a wayward thirtysomething man masquerading as a lone parent in a bid to seduce single mothers. Ironically, it is the boy who initiates the bachelor into the world of adult responsibility and meaningful relationships as the bond between them deepens

programme.title: The Thin Red Line
programme.desc: World War II epic follows a squad of GIs advancing on Guadalcanal. One solider, Private Witt, is a deserter living in peace and harmony with the natives of a Pacific island paradise. However, Witt's respite from war is brief as he's captured by the Navy and forced back into combat

programme.title: The Client
programme.desc: An 11-year-old boy, who has witnessed a suicide, hires an attorney to protect himself and his family from mobsters

programme.title: Kinsey
programme.desc: Provocative, intelligent biopic starring Liam Neeson as pioneering sex researcher Alfred Kinsey and Laura Linney as his freethinking wife. Chris O'Donnell, Peter Sarsgaard, Timothy Hutton, John Lithgow, Tim Curry. Directed by Bill Condon

programme.title: Elizabeth
programme.desc: Cate Blanchett reprises her role as Queen Elizabeth I in this account of her efforts to defend England from King Philip II of Spain, while trying to suppress her attraction to the dashing Sir Walter Raleigh

programme.title: In the Valley of Elah
programme.desc: Riveting fact-based drama about a Vietnam war veteran (Tommy Lee Jones) who goes on a quest to find his soldier son, who disappeared after returning stateside from a tour of duty in Iraq. Susan Sarandon, Charlize Theron. Written and directed by Paul Haggis

programme.title: Confidence
programme.desc: Well-made but derivative crime drama about a cocky grifter (Edward Burns) trying to make amends after accidentally ripping off a powerful L.A. underworld boss (Dustin Hoffman). Directed by James Foley. Screenplay by Doug Jung

programme.title: Swimming With Sharks
programme.desc: A recent film-school grad gets a dream job as a personal assistant to a Hollywood mogul, who not only tyrannizes him, but also takes credit for his script

programme.title: Wilson
programme.desc: A salty curmudgeon who is discontentment with how his life has stalled is shocked to discover he has a now-teenage daughter put up for adoption by his ex-wife after their split. He tries to reunite the family, but his abrasive personality makes getting reacquainted unpleasant for everyone

programme.title: Ghosts of Girlfriends Past
programme.desc: Successful fashion photographer and confirmed womanizer Connor Mead (Matthew McConaughey) has learned everything he knows about women from his deceased uncle Wayne (Michael Douglas). As his brother is about to get married, Connor takes a break from his playboy lifestyle to attend the ceremony not without first trying to convince his sibling of the enormous mistake he is about to make. After a drunken speech at the rehearsal dinner, Connor meets in the bathroom the ghost of Uncle Wayne, who surprisingly shows his regret and tells his nephew that, over the course of the evening, he'll be visited by three ghosts who will lead him through his romantic past, present, and future. Will this be Connor¿s big chance to get over himself and find true love?

programme.title: Spies Like Us
programme.desc: Two misfit low-level CIA agents are turned into decoys by their superiors and sent to Pakistan to distract Soviet agents from discovering the genuine American spies in the area. However, the two bumbling buddies end up making more of a difference in the cold war than anyone expects

programme.title: Jackass
programme.desc: Johnny Knoxville and his gang of merry pranksters perform a series of rude and crude stunts. Included: destructive shenanigans with golf carts. Performers include Steve-O, Chris Pontius, Bam Margera, Dave England, Ryan Dunn and Jason Acuña. Inspired by the MTV series

programme.title: Surviving Christmas
programme.desc: A lonely ad exec (Ben Affleck) offers to pay the sullen owners of his childhood home to let him spend the holidays there. This uneven comedy lacks comfort and joy. James Gandolfini, Catherine O'Hara. Mike Mitchell directed

programme.title: Here on Earth
programme.desc: After crashing his car in a small town, a spoiled rich kid falls for a local beauty but faces competition from her boyfriend

programme.title: Erin Brockovich
programme.desc: Erin Brockovich is an unemployed single mother, desperate to find a job, but is having no luck.While no one takes her seriously, with her trashy clothes and earthy manners, that soon changes when she begins to investigate a suspicious real estate case involving the Pacific Gas & Electric Company. What she discovers is that the company is trying quietly to buy land that was contaminated by hexavalent chromium, and, in turn, poisoning the residents in the area. As she digs deeper, Erin finds herself leading point in a series of events that would involve her lawfirm in one of the biggest class action lawsuits in American history against a multi-billion dollar corporation

programme.title: Happy Tears
programme.desc: Sisters Jayne (Parker Posey) and Laura (Demi Moore) reunite in Pittsburgh to care for their father, whose poor health hasn't stopped him from pursuing a romance with a suspicious woman (Ellen Barkin), much to the consternation of the two sisters. Rip Torn

programme.title: Addicted to Love
programme.desc: Good-natured astronomer Sam is devastated when the love of his life, Linda, leaves him for a suave Frenchman named Anton. He therefore does what every other normal dumpee would do; go to New York and set up home in the abandoned building opposite his exgirlfriend's apartment, intent on winning her back and waiting until she decides to leave her current lover. What Sam does not count on is being joined several weeks later by ultra hip tomboy Maggie, a photographer and motorcyclist who is determined to get revenge on Anton, her ex-fiance. Hostile at first, the two of them eventually join forces in an attempt to separate the couple, and ruin Anton's life. However, complications ensue when Sam and Maggie start falling for each other

programme.title: Fried Green Tomatoes
programme.desc: Kathy Bates and Jessica Tandy head a fine cast in this story of female friendships in the South. Contains footage not shown in theaters. Idgie: Mary Stuart Masterson. Ruth: Mary-Louise Parker. Sipsey: Cicely Tyson. George: Stan Shaw. Frank: Nick Searcy. Ed: Gailard Sartain. Grady: Gary Basaraba. Buddy: Chris O'Donnell. Directed by Jon Avnet from a screenplay by Fannie Flagg and Carol Sobieski

programme.title: The Zookeeper's Wife
programme.desc: A husband and wife in Nazi-occupied Poland use their position as caretakers at the Warsaw Zoo to shepherd Jews out of the country. Based on the non-fiction book by Diane Ackerman ("A Natural History of the Senses")(n)

programme.title: A Walk in the Clouds
programme.desc: Alfonso Arau's delight of a romantic film, made after Like Water for Chocolate, opens with Paul Sutton returning home after World War II to a wife he married the day before he left. Discovering they have nothing in common, he leaves for home by bus. Among the passengers is Victoria Aragón, who is afraid to go home to her family's vineyards because she is pregnant and unmarried. Paul suggests they pretend to be a married couple, to conceal her situation. When they arrive at her home, her father Alberto and his wife María are stern and suspicious, as is patriarch Don Pedro, but as the days stretch into weeks, Paul falls for Victoria, her family and their way of life... Edited for content(n)

programme.title: Cake

programme.title: Secretary

Searching for work, she takes a lowly clerical job with dour, demanding attorney James Spader. Critical of her mistakes, one day, verbal abuse crosses to physical, as he spanks her. But she seems to thrive on his treatment and a reciprocal relationship begins until Spader, finding she enjoys the humiliation, fires her. Bereft, and with her boyfriend Jeremy Davies unable to fulfil her desires, she plans to win back Spader's affections. Steven Shainberg's film could have been crudely exploitative but thanks to the delicacy of his treatment, the subtlety of the two central performances, plus a leavening of humour, this is a story of unconventional love but love for all that

The film follows Cash from his childhood, where he was touched by tragedy, through his years on the road to his marriage to June Carter, who was country royalty (having been a part of the massively influential Carter Family band), and their struggle to find happiness as she weans him off booze and drugs. Walk the Line is a warts-and-all biopic, showing Cash's faults as well as his undoubted star quality as one of the greatest singer/songwriters that America has ever produced(n)

programme.title: Almost Famous
programme.desc: Written and directed by Cameron Crowe, Almost Famous tells the story of a 15-year-old boy who, in the early '70s, is given the opportunity to go on tour with a rock band. William Miller's mother is overly obsessed with drugs and the negative influence of rock on teenagers. But he is a music lover and his hobby is to write about bands for an underground newspaper. The boy's work eventually catches the attention of Lester Bangs (Philip Seymor Hoffman), editor of a rock magazine who then asks him to cover a great concert. William manages to get only an interview with the opening band, Stillwater, but even so he wins the admiration of another editor, this time, of Rolling Stone. Now the boy has the opportunity to continue traveling with Stillwater and write an article that could open up the way to showbiz. During the tour he meets various interesting people, including a girl he falls in love with (Kate Hudson). Crowe, who received an Oscar for Best Screenplay for this film, wrote the story based on his teenage experiences, when he also contributed to Rolling Stone
